CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 13, 1954, pg. 14, reads: "In Carnation Contest - The King family will be well represented in Carnation Milk Company's Healthy Baby Contest. Entries are pouring in to beat the Nov. 17 deadline.  Five hundred dollars in cash prizes will be awarded the winning babies.  On the tricycles are twins Roger L. and Richard J., while little sister, Phyllis Ellen, smiles.  They are the children of Mrs. Evelyn King, 7955 Tioga Street. Fill out the coupon on this page. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Twins Roger L. and Richard J. King seated on tricycles, possibly in yard of their home at 7955 Tioga Street, Homewood
